---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../../data/apps';
---

<Base
  title="Masbaha — Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for the Masbaha app: no personal data collected; all data stays on your device."
>
  <div class="container">
    <article class="prose">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted small">Last updated: July 7, 2026</p>

      <p>
        We built the <strong>Masbaha</strong> app as a free, ad-supported
        application. This page informs you of our policies regarding the
        collection, use, and disclosure of information when you use our app.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        Masbaha does <strong>not</strong> collect, store, or transmit any
        personal information. The app does not require an account, login, or
        any form of registration.
      </p>

      <h2>Local Data Storage</h2>
      <p>The app stores the following data locally on your device only:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Bead counter value</li>
        <li>Tasbeeh plans and progress</li>
        <li>App settings and preferences (sound, vibration, trigger level, background image, bead design)</li>
        <li>Daily reminder times</li>
        <li>A record of which bead designs you have purchased (product identifiers only — no payment details)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data is stored using your device's local storage and is never sent
        to any server. You can clear this data at any time by clearing the
        app's data or uninstalling the app.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>The app uses the following third-party services that may collect information:</p>

      <h3>Google AdMob</h3>
      <p>
        We use Google AdMob to display advertisements. AdMob may collect and
        use data to serve personalized or non-personalized ads. This may
        include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Device identifiers</li>
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Usage data</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        For more information on how Google uses data, please visit:
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          Google Advertising Privacy Policy</a>
      </p>

      <h3>Google Play Billing (In-App Purchases)</h3>
      <p>
        On Android, optional bead designs can be bought as one-time in-app
        purchases. Payments are processed entirely by
        <strong>Google Play</strong>; the app never sees or stores your payment
        details (card numbers, billing address, etc.). Google Play may process
        personal data as part of the transaction as described in the
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          Google Privacy Policy</a>. The app only stores, locally on your
        device, which designs you own so they stay unlocked offline. Purchases
        are tied to your Google account and can be restored on any device using
        the same account.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our app does not knowingly collect personal information from children.
        Since we do not collect any personal data, the app is safe for users of
        all ages.
      </p>

      <h2>Permissions</h2>
      <p>The app may request the following permissions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Vibration</strong> — to provide haptic feedback when counting beads</li>
        <li><strong>Internet</strong> — required for displaying advertisements</li>
        <li><strong>Notifications</strong> — for daily tasbeeh reminders (optional)</li>
        <li><strong>Photo library</strong> — to select a custom background image (optional)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data Deletion</h2>
      <p>All app data is stored locally on your device. You can delete all data at any time by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Going to your device's <strong>Settings → Apps → Masbaha → Clear Data</strong></li>
        <li>Uninstalling the app</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Since we do not store any data on external servers, no further action
        is needed to delete your information.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will
        be reflected on this page with an updated date.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at:</p>
      <p><a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a></p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>
